{
  "rule": "divergence_arakawa_c",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "expected_min_order": 1.9,
  "notes": "Centered two-point finite-volume divergence on the Arakawa C-grid is theoretically O(h^2) when the velocity field is smooth and the grid is uniform. The vec_sincos_2d_periodic manufactured solution F = (sin(2π x) cos(2π y), cos(2π x) sin(2π y)) on [0,1]² has analytic divergence ∇·F = 4π cos(2π x) cos(2π y); both components vary non-trivially in both axes so the sweep exercises the face_x and face_y stencil arms. Threshold 1.9 leaves a 0.1 margin below the declared O(h^2) order to absorb pre-asymptotic drift on the n=16->32->64->128 sequence; the harness's own ±0.2 tolerance band keeps superconvergence ungated. Driven by EarthSciSerialization.apply_stencil_2d_arakawa via the kind:'arakawa' selector dispatch (esm-x9f); both axes wrap periodically per the C-grid convention."
}
